{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"47d8be472a62e033a34ab7f54e5875ee1a1f0e6dec0aae2580329b4b547064fd","slug":"xradioandcheckboxes","location":"/xRadioandCheckBoxes.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Radio and Check Boxes","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"James Goudy","given":"James","family":"Goudy"},"name":"James Goudy","id":"contributors-a_books\\csci211_csbook\\myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/executablebooks/jupyter-book","keywords":["JavaScript","TypeScript"],"copyright":"2026","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"xRadioandCheckBoxes.md","url":"/CSCI211/build/xRadioandCheckBoxes-d938eadaa7b2d94ab3c3f141e189781d.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Radio buttons and checkboxes are two of the most common ways a web page collects “choice” input, but they behave very differently: radios enforce a single decision inside a shared group (only one option can be selected at a time), while checkboxes allow multiple independent selections (zero, one, or many). This example demonstrates both patterns in one clean page: the radio section listens for ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"HrmzV4DQNF"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"change","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"ZCfIQe8OZH"},{"type":"text","value":" events and uses ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"OcHHT8N1JW"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"document.querySelector('input[name=\"grp1\"]:checked')","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"RjONIoDX5a"},{"type":"text","value":" to grab the one currently-selected radio and immediately print a message, while the checkbox section waits for a button click, uses ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"f9V7FN3e4k"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"document.querySelectorAll('input[type=\"checkbox\"]:checked')","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"ViJkIOXS31"},{"type":"text","value":" to gather every checked box, and then builds a readable summary by matching each checkbox to its ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"gvrtabCmlA"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"<label>","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"Y2hQZL2XOj"},{"type":"text","value":" via ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"PPItBahaOI"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"label[for=\"...\"]","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"QllDKvlXkg"},{"type":"text","value":". In other words, the DOM becomes a searchable map: ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"DWVeKfv9ET"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"querySelector","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"yl7Eo2y5kS"},{"type":"text","value":" is your “find the first match” tool for single answers (the selected radio), and ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"gNU5neQyvO"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"querySelectorAll","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"FXU7l0Ey42"},{"type":"text","value":" is your “collect all matches” tool for plural answers (the checked checkboxes).","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"APe4WFbb22"}],"key":"N5CLztbSKv"},{"type":"code","lang":"javascript","value":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n  <title>Radio + Checkbox Demo</title>\n\n  <style>\n    .div1 {\n            width: 75%;\n            background-color: cornsilk;\n            padding: 20px;\n            margin-left: auto;\n            margin-right: auto;\n            margin-top: 50px;\n            margin-bottom: 50px;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n  <div class=\"div1\">\n    <h1>Radio Buttons</h1>\n\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"rad1\" name=\"grp1\" value=\"10\" />\n    <label for=\"rad1\">Option 1</label><br />\n\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"rad2\" name=\"grp1\" value=\"20\" checked />\n    <label for=\"rad2\">Option 2</label><br />\n\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"rad3\" name=\"grp1\" value=\"30\" />\n    <label for=\"rad3\">Option 3</label><br />\n\n    <br />\n    <hr />\n    <br />\n\n    <h1>Check Boxes</h1>\n\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"cb1\" name=\"cbgrp\" value=\"11\" />\n    <label for=\"cb1\">check box 1</label><br />\n\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"cb2\" name=\"cbgrp\" value=\"22\" />\n    <label for=\"cb2\">check box 2</label><br />\n\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"cb3\" name=\"cbgrp\" value=\"33\" />\n    <label for=\"cb3\">check box 3</label><br /><br />\n\n    <input type=\"button\" value=\"Show selected checkboxes\" onclick=\"checkboxCheck()\" />\n\n    <br /><br />\n    <hr />\n    <br />\n\n    <p id=\"radioMess\"></p>\n    <p id=\"checkMess\"></p>\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n      \n    function updateRadioMessage() {\n        \n      // Select the first thing that is named \"grp1\" that is checked\n      const selected = document.querySelector('input[name=\"grp1\"]:checked');\n      const radioOut = document.getElementById(\"radioMess\");\n\n      if (!selected) {\n        radioOut.textContent = \"No radio option selected.\";\n        return;\n      }\n\n      let message;\n      if (selected.value === \"10\") message = \"rad1 selected (value 10)\";\n      else if (selected.value === \"20\") message = \"rad2 selected (value 20)\";\n      else message = \"rad3 selected (value 30)\";\n\n      radioOut.textContent = message;\n    }\n\n    function checkboxCheck() {\n        \n      // all of the selected checkboxes are collected and put into an array checkedBoxes  \n      const checkedBoxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type=\"checkbox\"]:checked');\n      console.log(checkedBoxes);\n\n      const checkOut = document.getElementById(\"checkMess\");\n\n      // nothing has been checked\n      if (checkedBoxes.length === 0) {\n        checkOut.textContent = \"No checkboxes selected.\";\n        return;\n      }\n\n      let message = \"Checked: \";\n\n      for (let i = 0; i < checkedBoxes.length; i++) {\n        const cb = checkedBoxes[i];\n\n        const label = document.querySelector('label[for=\"' + cb.id + '\"]');\n\n        let labelText;\n        if (label) {\n          labelText = label.textContent.trim();\n        } else {\n          labelText = cb.id;\n        }\n\n        if (i > 0) {\n          message += \", \";\n        }\n\n        message += labelText + \" (value \" + cb.value + \")\";\n      }\n\n      checkOut.textContent = message;\n    }\n\n    // add listeners for radio buttons\n    document.querySelectorAll('input[name=\"grp1\"]').forEach(radio => {\n      radio.addEventListener(\"change\", updateRadioMessage);\n    });\n\n    // add listeners for check boxes\n    document.querySelectorAll('input[name=\"cbgrp\"]').forEach(checkbox=>{\n            checkbox.addEventListener(\"change\",checboxCheck);\n    });\n\n    updateRadioMessage();\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":141,"column":1}},"key":"YWkzZzF2HU"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":143,"column":1},"end":{"line":143,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Document.querySelector","position":{"start":{"line":143,"column":1},"end":{"line":143,"column":1}},"key":"ing33MAWMr"}],"identifier":"document-queryselector","label":"Document.querySelector","html_id":"document-queryselector","implicit":true,"key":"Psd5j8L8pP"},{"type":"paragraph","po